ulation. In the UK, a disease is considered rare if it affects fewer than 1 in 2,000 people.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-1066_"><b>Rare Disease Day</b> - Rare Disease Day is an international observance held annually on the last day of February to raise awareness about rare diseases and the challenges faced by individuals and families affected by these conditions.</li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-1068_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/doctor-examining-baby-12-17-months-2023-11-27-05-33-24-utc.jpg?v=1710238134" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/doctor-examining-baby-12-17-months-2023-11-27-05-33-24-utc.jpg?v=1710238134 1536w" width="1000" height="694" alt="Rare Disease Day: Raising Awareness for Orphan Diseases - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="Rare Disease Day: Raising Awareness for Orphan Diseases - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-1069_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-1070_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by astrakanimages via Envato Elements</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-1072_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-1073_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/small-black-circle-with-the-word-awareness-the-co-2023-11-27-05-33-59-utc_3.jpg?v=1710239076" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/small-black-circle-with-the-word-awareness-the-co-2023-11-27-05-33-59-utc_3.jpg?v=1710239076 1536w" width="1000" height="666" alt="Genetic Disorders: Supporting Rare Disease Day Initiatives - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - 