their rights and contribute to positive change on a local, national, and global scale.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-1184_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-1185_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-1186_">Support and resources</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/alphabet-letters-with-supporting-words-2023-11-27-04-54-11-utc_1.jpg?v=1710239292" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/alphabet-letters-with-supporting-words-2023-11-27-04-54-11-utc_1.jpg?v=1710239292 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/alphabet-letters-with-supporting-words-2023-11-27-04-54-11-utc_1_1000x.jpg?v=1710239292 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/alphabet-letters-with-supporting-words-2023-11-27-04-54-11-utc_1_500x.jpg?v=1710239292 320w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Rare Disease Support: Empowering the Rare Disease Community - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="Rare Disease Support: Empowering the Rare Disease Community - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-1188_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-1189_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by fauziEv8 via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-1191_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">For individuals and families affected by rare diseases, navigating the complexities of diagnosis, treatment, and care can be daunting. Thankfully, there are organisations and resources available to provide support and guidance. Whether it's connecting with patient support groups, accessing informational resources, or seeking assistance with navigating healthcare systems, organisations like Rare Diseases UK, Genetic Alliance UK, EURORDIS, NORD, and The Mandatory Training Group are valuable sources of support for the rare disease community.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-1193_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-1194_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-1195_">Key facts and statistics</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mohdizzuanbinroslan_de0e57cd-a4f8-47de-9af6-73092bf2ab0b.jpg?v=1710236082" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mohdizzuanbinroslan_de0e57cd-a4f8-47de-9af6-73092bf2ab0b.jpg?v=1710236082 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mohdizzuanbinroslan_de0e57cd-a4f8-47de-9af6-73092bf2ab0b_1000x.jpg?v=1710236082 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/mohdizzuanbinroslan_de0e57cd-a4f8-47de-9af6-73092bf2ab0b_500x.jpg?v=1710236082 320w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Rare Disease Research: Advancing Treatment Options - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="Rare Disease Research: Advancing Treatment Options - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-1197_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-1198_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by mohdizzuanbinroslan via Envato Elements</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-1200_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-1201_">Rare diseases collectively impact millions of individuals worldwide, with estimates suggesting that over 300 million people are affected globally.
